The paper focuses on graph representation learning of heterogeneous information networks (HIN) using a novel attention-based graph neural network. This topic falls under the broad category of machine learning and artificial intelligence, which is covered by cs.LG and cs.AI. The paper also discusses the use of attention mechanisms and multi-task learning, which are common techniques in natural language processing and information retrieval, covered by cs.SI and cs.IR. Finally, the paper deals with the aggregation of multi-relational information, which is a common problem in database systems, covered by cs.DB. Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.LG and cs.AI, followed by cs.SI, cs.IR, and cs.DB.
